What I did was I specified looking at the type column using pandas dataframes in order to see what types of stops they were making. I then added up all the values for each variable in the column which turned out to be Vehicular and Pedestrian. Then I divided those values by the total number of cases in order to get a percentage in how each of the types compare to each other.¶

In [1]:
import csv

def make_data_point(line, header):
    output = {}
    for index, header_item in enumerate(header):
        output[header_item] = line[index]
    return output

with open("denver-1.nov.csv") as inf:
    reader = csv.reader(inf)
    header = next(reader)
    all_data = []
    for line in reader:
        all_data.append(make_data_point(line, header))
In [2]:
from collections import defaultdict

# this stores a dictionary mapping each precinct to a list of data
# from that precinct
byprecinct = defaultdict(list)  
for line in all_data:
    byprecinct[line["precinct"]].append(line)
